commit.message: setInterval doesn't seem to like long numbers for interval counter, yet basic math helps the pill go down apparently.
Fixes bug where res was set after sent. Also, creates auto data creation once every 20 minutes to keep data alive long after I leave the app alone.
Keeps the header setting right away to avoid possible no set after send errors.
Fixes function name typo and some spawn settings.
Separates the data generator out into its own file.
Recombines the observation data back into those that had object types for observation.
Changed file name and exported object name to better capture the service's purpose.
Implements the complete data pull for Today, Week, and Month.
Finishes implementing all the PUT endpoints, and building all related tables.
Cleans up A LOT, documents better, and solidifies the ability to get data by today, week, month, and put for scent, water-clarity, and vegetation.
First major push that includes the GET for 'today' data, and POST for 'scent' observations.
